// auto-continue cold-worktree-spawn focus fix (2026-06-03).
// A fresh per-session worktree window opens with the LEFT sidebar (Explorer) focused, so a synthetic
// `keystroke return` lands on the sidebar — NOT the Claude input (which renders in the side panel).
// auto-continue.sh sends this chord (HANDOFF_FOCUS_KEY=0 + ctrl/alt/cmd) right before the Enter to run
// Claude Code's "Focus input" command (claude-vscode.focus has a built-in cmd+escape binding but it is
// gated on `editorTextFocus`, so it does NOT fire from the sidebar — hence this UNCONDITIONAL binding).
// Merge this object into ~/Library/Application Support/Code/User/keybindings.json (the array).
[
  {
    "key": "ctrl+alt+cmd+0",
    "command": "claude-vscode.focus"
  }
]
